{"id":686,"date":"2022-01-06T17:10:21","date_gmt":"2022-01-06T17:10:21","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=686"},"modified":"2022-01-10T19:11:09","modified_gmt":"2022-01-10T19:11:09","slug":"use-grep-and-regular-expressions-to-analyze-text","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=686","title":{"rendered":"Use grep and regular expressions to analyze text"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h3>What are Linux Regular Expressions?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Linux Regular Expressions<\/strong> are special characters which help search data and matching complex patterns. Regular expressions are shortened as \u2018regexp\u2019 or \u2018regex\u2019. They are used in many Linux programs like g<strong>rep, bash, rename, sed, etc.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Basic Regular expressions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the commonly used commands with Regular expressions are tr, sed, vi and grep. Listed below are some of the basic Regex.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/lh3.googleusercontent.com\/HFwlWgJ7YLBkV35TWmb9DnQZ_g6m1Cun7a5FTsF0Wu6gNuY-40Bf2_Tz5g2yy-NvODABhMQUAcyDxTd70A00VWjqREfQzrNH9pifDOfpvRPcM4ZdOQj-gRV1rh2VqocrxjsD57Lo\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s demonstrate this on the example. Because we all love pizza, I&#8217;ve created a file containing pizza ingredients called example.txt.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"116\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-52.png?resize=640%2C116&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-689\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-52.png?w=841&amp;ssl=1 841w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-52.png?resize=300%2C55&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-52.png?resize=768%2C140&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-52.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-52.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-52.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, let&#8217;s say you would only want to list ingredient that has a letter &#8220;o&#8221; inside. You would do this with grep and regular expression that looks like this:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">cat example.txt | grep o<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"74\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-53.png?resize=640%2C74&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-690\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-53.png?w=699&amp;ssl=1 699w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-53.png?resize=300%2C35&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-53.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-53.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-53.png?resize=48%2C6&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Or maybe you only want to see words that end with a letter &#8220;s&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\"> cat example.txt | grep s$<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"502\" height=\"56\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-54.png?resize=502%2C56&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-691\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-54.png?w=502&amp;ssl=1 502w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-54.png?resize=300%2C33&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-54.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-54.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-54.png?resize=48%2C5&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 502px) 100vw, 502px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>The possibilities or regular expressions or so-called regex are pretty much endless.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Interval Regular expressions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>These expressions tell us about the number of occurrences of a character in a string. They are <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/lh6.googleusercontent.com\/QNUKKD_3YnxVVX_sHVT4gKCdLX1YbtEVp65yf8kkLmi7Xl5IO65jMyujeALh51UTzD2xva7EVjKHxc84PWKHlr2cjVLdQMUQMpIk2v9_upNQXbfNnKOS5ck5Fqh8sXt7rgLAKBjC\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s for an example check if character &#8220;p&#8221; appears exactly 2 times in a string, one after the other<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">cat example.txt | grep -E p\\{2}<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"561\" height=\"95\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-50.png?resize=561%2C95&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-687\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-50.png?w=561&amp;ssl=1 561w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-50.png?resize=300%2C51&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-50.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-50.png?resize=36%2C6&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-50.png?resize=48%2C8&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 561px) 100vw, 561px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Brace expansion<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The syntax for brace expansion is either a sequence or a <strong>comma <\/strong>&#8220;,&#8221; separated list of items inside curly braces \u201c{}\u201d. The starting and ending items in a sequence are separated by <strong>two periods<\/strong> \u201c..\u201d.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"133\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-55.png?resize=640%2C133&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-692\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-55.png?w=830&amp;ssl=1 830w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-55.png?resize=300%2C62&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-55.png?resize=768%2C159&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-55.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-55.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-55.png?resize=48%2C10&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Few more useful examples of file globing<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">ls host*<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">ls ?ost<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">ls [hm]ost<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">ls [!hm]ost&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">ls script [0-9] [0-9]<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>What are Linux Regular Expressions? Linux Regular Expressions are special characters which help search data [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":751,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[243,240,242,220,239],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-understand-and-use-essential-tools-2.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/686"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=686"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/686\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":758,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/686\/revisions\/758"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/751"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=686"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcategories&post=686"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Ftags&post=686"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}